commit.message: Incorporate srfi-252 tests from reference impl

srfi.252 - Adding testing procedures

NB: This currently works with gauche.test, but it does not update
srfi-64 test result counts, and it may confuse if this is used
in a 3rd party code that assumes srfi-64.  We need to work on it.

srfi.64 - Omit reference impl's logging feature

Reference implementation has logging feature in test-runner-simple.
It is not specified in srfi text, and it is unnecessary as long as
srfi.64 is used with gauche.test, so we dropped that feature.
This also avoids scattering *.log file all over the source tree.

gauche.test - Keep filename for nesting tests

Instead of just a nesting count, keep the test name and filename
stack in *test-nesting*.  We can later associate that info with
the discrepancy list, so that it would be easier to see which
file has the failed test, in case if test files are nested.

sxml.tools - Fix sxml:sxml->html

The original sxml-tools is a simple wrapper to treat SXML as html
tree.  But HTML is not exactly XML, and requires more specific handling.

- HTML doesn't have namespaces.  So, if an attribute name contains a colon,
  it's a part of the name; render it as is.
- HTML doesn't have self-closing elements (but it has void elements).
  So, non-void elements with empty content should be rendered
  as <foo></foo>.
